text: Kenmoor is an unincorporated community in Buchanan County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Kenmoor was established in 1886, and remained in operation until 1904. The community was named for a local businessman in the telephony industry. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Buchanan County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Kenmoor, Missouri
